Courses are about systems, networks, security and forensic analysis. In the Forensics track you will learn how to gather relevant information from large amounts of unknown data and present it in a usable way to criminal investigators. The Networking track will teach you about very large scale networks and the problems that come with them. You will also get aquainted with the scientific method and research your own topics during two one-month projects. In your research, you can work together with our faculty's top-notch systems and network engineering group.]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[How do you apply different software components within a complex architecture, such that you get an efficiently working system? How do you make a system that not only technicians, but everyone can use? Together with a experienced teaching staff and highly motivated fellow-students you look at the many software systems that exist and wonder how to get all these systems connected in a way that's practical, safe and scalable.

